# Terms and Conditions for Consultancy Services

## 1. Definitions

**Consultant** means the party providing the services.
**Client** means the party receiving the services.
**Services** means the consultancy work described in the proposal or scope document.
**Deliverables** means any outputs supplied to the client as part of the services.
**Agreement** means these terms and the accompanying proposal.

## 2. Engagement

The client engages the consultant to provide the services. The consultant will perform the services with reasonable skill and care. The consultant will work with the client to agree the scope, timelines and expected outcomes for each phase.

## 3. Client Responsibilities

The client will

* provide access to information, systems and people needed for the services
* ensure that decisions are made in a timely manner
* take responsibility for how any deliverables are used in their business
* provide a single point of contact for communication and approvals

## 4. Fees and Payment

Fees are set out in the proposal. Invoices are payable within fourteen days unless agreed otherwise. Travel or third party costs will be charged at cost with prior approval. Late payment may result in work being paused until payment is received.

## 5. Changes to Scope

Any change to the agreed scope must be confirmed in writing. The consultant will advise of any impact on cost or timeline. Work will only proceed once the change is agreed by both parties.

## 6. Confidentiality

Each party will keep all confidential information safe and will only use it for the purpose of this agreement. Confidentiality continues after the agreement ends.

## 7. Intellectual Property

The consultant retains ownership of all background materials, methods and tools used in the delivery. The client receives a licence to use the deliverables for their internal business purposes. Any bespoke materials created specifically for the client will belong to the client once payment is complete.

## 8. Data Protection

Both parties will comply with all applicable data protection laws. If the services require access to personal data, a data processing arrangement will be agreed.

## 9. Liability

The consultant is not liable for indirect or consequential loss. The consultant’s total liability for any claim arising from this agreement will not exceed the total fees paid in the previous three months. Nothing in this agreement limits liability for fraud or anything else that cannot be excluded by law.

## 10. Termination

Either party may terminate with thirty days’ notice. Either party may terminate immediately if the other party commits a serious breach that is not corrected within fourteen days. The client will pay for all work completed up to the termination date.

## 11. Independent Contractor

The consultant is an independent contractor. Nothing in this agreement creates an employment relationship, partnership or joint venture.

## 12. Non Solicitation

The client will not solicit or employ the consultant’s staff or subcontractors for twelve months after the end of the agreement without written consent.

## 13. Force Majeure

Neither party will be liable for delays caused by events outside their reasonable control. The affected party will notify the other and take reasonable steps to minimise impact.

## 14. Governing Law

This agreement is governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes will be resolved in the courts of England and Wales.

## 15. Entire Agreement

This agreement and the proposal form the entire agreement between the parties. Any amendments must be made in writing.

---

