Standard Consulting Services Agreement: Terms and Conditions

These Standard Terms and Conditions (the "Terms") govern the engagement between the Client and the Consultant for the provision of professional consulting services, including digital strategy and transformation services.

1. Definitions

Term

Definition

Consultant

The consulting firm or individual providing the Services, as defined in the associated SOW.

Client

The legal entity engaging the Consultant for the Services.

Services

The professional services, advice, and deliverables provided by the Consultant to the Client, as detailed in the applicable Statement of Work (SOW).

Deliverables

Any work product, documents, reports, models, code, or materials prepared by the Consultant specifically for the Client as part of the Services.

Confidential Information

Any non-public information, including trade secrets, financial data, business plans, and customer information, disclosed by one party to the other.

Consultant IP

All Intellectual Property (IP) owned or licensed by the Consultant prior to or independently of this Agreement, including methodologies, tools, software, templates, and frameworks used in providing the Services.

2. Scope of Services

2.1. Engagement. The Consultant agrees to provide the Services to the Client as described and limited in a separate written Statement of Work (SOW), which will be attached hereto and incorporated by reference. Each SOW must be mutually executed by both parties.

2.2. Digital Transformation Focus. The Services, particularly those related to Digital Transformation, are advisory in nature and involve providing recommendations, strategies, and implementation support. The Client retains ultimate responsibility for all implementation decisions and outcomes.

2.3. Changes to Scope. Any changes, additions, or modifications to the Services or Deliverables must be agreed upon in writing via a formal Change Order executed by both parties, which may result in adjustments to the fees and/or timeline.

3. Fees, Invoicing, and Payment

3.1. Fees. The Client will pay the Consultant the fees specified in the applicable SOW. Unless otherwise stated in the SOW, fees will be invoiced monthly in arrears based on actual time spent at the agreed-upon hourly rates, or as milestone payments for fixed-price projects.

3.2. Invoicing and Payment Terms. Invoices are due and payable Net 30 days from the invoice date.

3.3. Late Payments. If any payment is not received by the due date, the Consultant may charge interest on the overdue amount at a rate of 1.5% per month, or the maximum rate permitted by law, whichever is lower. The Consultant may also suspend the provision of Services until payment is made in full.

3.4. Expenses. The Client will reimburse the Consultant for all reasonable and necessary out-of-pocket expenses incurred in providing the Services, including travel, lodging, and materials, provided such expenses are documented and in compliance with the Client's travel policy (if provided in advance).

4. Intellectual Property (IP)

4.1. Consultant IP. All Consultant IP remains the sole and exclusive property of the Consultant. The Consultant grants the Client a non-exclusive, non-transferable, royalty-free license to use the Consultant IP solely as necessary for the Client to use and benefit from the Deliverables.

4.2. Deliverables IP. Upon the Client's full and final payment of all fees and expenses due under the applicable SOW, the Consultant hereby assigns all rights, title, and interest in and to the Deliverables to the Client. The Client shall be the sole owner of the Deliverables.

4.3. Client IP. All data, materials, documents, and intellectual property provided by the Client to the Consultant for use in connection with the Services remain the exclusive property of the Client.

5. Confidentiality

5.1. Obligation. Each party agrees not to disclose, divulge, or use the Confidential Information of the other party for any purpose other than fulfilling the obligations under this Agreement. This obligation remains in effect for a period of three (3) years following the termination of this Agreement.

5.2. Exclusions. The obligations of confidentiality do not apply to information that: (a) is or becomes publicly known through no fault of the receiving party; (b) was known to the receiving party before disclosure; (c) is disclosed to the receiving party by a third party without breach of confidentiality; or (d) is required to be disclosed by law or court order, provided the disclosing party is given reasonable notice to seek a protective order.

6. Warranties and Limitation of Liability

6.1. Consultant Warranty. The Consultant warrants that the Services will be performed in a professional and workmanlike manner, in accordance with generally accepted industry standards.

6.2. DISCLAIMER. EXCEPT FOR THE EXPRESS WARRANTY SET FORTH IN SECTION 6.1, THE SERVICES AND DELIVERABLES ARE PROVIDED "AS IS." THE CONSULTANT DISCLAIMS ALL OTHER WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.

6.3. Limitation of Liability. NEITHER PARTY SHALL BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, SPECIAL, PUNITIVE, OR EXEMPLARY DAMAGES (INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, LOST REVENUE, LOST PROFITS, OR LOSS OF DATA) ARISING OUT OF OR RELATING TO THIS AGREEMENT, REGARDLESS OF THE FORM OF ACTION, EVEN IF THE PARTY KNEW OR SHOULD HAVE KNOWN OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.

6.4. Cap on Liability. The total liability of the Consultant for any claim arising out of or relating to this Agreement, whether in contract, tort, or otherwise, shall not exceed the total fees paid by the Client to the Consultant under the applicable SOW during the six (6) months immediately preceding the event giving rise to the claim.

7. Term and Termination

7.1. Term. This Agreement commences on the date of execution and continues until terminated as set forth herein.

7.2. Termination for Convenience. Either party may terminate any SOW for convenience upon thirty (30) days written notice to the other party.

7.3. Termination for Cause. Either party may terminate this Agreement or any SOW immediately upon written notice if the other party materially breaches any provision of this Agreement or the SOW and fails to cure such breach within fifteen (15) days after receiving written notice thereof.

7.4. Effect of Termination. Upon termination, the Client shall pay the Consultant for all Services rendered and all expenses incurred up to the effective date of termination. Sections 1, 3, 4, 5, 6, and 8 shall survive the termination of this Agreement.

8. General Provisions

8.1. Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of [Insert Jurisdiction, e.g., the State of New York], without regard to its conflicts of law principles.

8.2. Independent Contractor. The Consultant is an independent contractor and not an employee, partner, or agent of the Client. The Consultant is solely responsible for all taxes and withholdings related to the compensation paid to the Consultant.

8.3. Force Majeure. Neither party shall be liable for any failure to perform its obligations (other than payment obligations) where such failure results from events beyond its reasonable control, including but not limited to, acts of nature, war, terrorism, and government restrictions.

8.4. Entire Agreement. This Agreement, together with all executed SOWs, constitutes the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes all prior agreements, oral or written, concerning the subject matter hereof.

----

